and provide some of the benefits that we've been hearing already. And then ultimately, at MAPC, we're providing the criteria that would go into the RFP focused on what those benefits are. After that, the city has its own steps where it needs to draft the RFP, it needs to surplus the property, and then actually issue the RFP itself. After that, so the process isn't done, once bids come in, there will be opportunities for the public to see what those bids are, we public, and then comment on those.

